hy_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":0.22,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"weak","read":"Only 0.22\u00d7 \u2014 profit not turning into cash (watch receivables/inventory).","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.58,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"good","read":"Conservatively financed (D/E 0.58\u00d7, interest cover 4.0\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":44.68,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 45% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":22.6,"pe_percentile":83.0,"median_pe":10.0,"earnings_yield_pct":4.42,"pb":4.43,"ev_ebitda":24.53,"quality_score":21.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 83-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 22.6\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not e